+# Phase 11 Slice Log
+
+## Metadata
+- **Persona:** Persona A: The Safe Grinder
+- **Slice Date:** 2026-03-21
+- **Week Covered:** Week 2
+- **Canonical Status:** authoritative
+- **Source Session:** `phase11-safe-grinder`
+
+## Start State
+- **Checkpoint:** Restored `docs/workflows/cyberpunk-overhaul/checkpoints/persona_a/week-01-save.json` after the live browser reopened at fresh onboarding instead of the expected Week 1 summary.
+- **Cash:** `₡172`
+- **Debt:** `₡0`
+- **Hunger:** `20%`
+- **Sanity:** `55`
+- **Education:** `0`
+- **Conditions:** none
+
+## Decisions & Path
+1. Verified the reopened browser had lost continuity (`WELCOME_TO_FASTLANE` with no `jones_fastlane_save`), then imported the authoritative Week 1 checkpoint instead of replaying from onboarding.
+2. Advanced from the Week 1 summary into Cycle 2, hit the opening `NETWORK STIMULUS DROP` event, and chose `REJECT: "KEEP YOUR SPYWARE."` as the Safe Grinder low-risk line.
+3. Re-entered Labor Sector, confirmed `Sanitation-T3` was still the active job, and completed the deterministic `Work Shift x3` route again with save-state time moving `22CH -> 16CH -> 10CH -> 4CH`.
+4. Returned to `Hab-Pod 404`, ended the week on the turn summary modal, captured evidence, and exported the authoritative Week 2 checkpoint before any Week 3 clicks.
+
+## Telemetry
+- **Gross Labor Yield:** `₡252`
+- **Burn Rate:** `₡80`
+- **End Cash:** `₡344`
+- **End Debt:** `₡0`
+- **End Hunger:** `40%`
+- **End Sanity:** `50`
+- **Education:** `0`
+- **Time Efficiency:** Week 2 preserved the same three-shift labor envelope as Week 1 even after the event prompt; Safe Grinder still finished the work loop with `4CH` remaining before heading home.
+- **Net Credits:** `+₡172`
+- **Net Sanity:** `+5`
+
+## High-Signal Findings
+- The restored Week 1 checkpoint was sufficient recovery when browser continuity failed. No replay-from-onboarding was needed once the save import landed the app back on the authoritative summary modal.
+- `NETWORK STIMULUS DROP` currently rewards the cautious rejection line with `+10 Sanity`, which more than offsets the weekly `Ambient Stress -10` and `Cycle Recovery +5` pattern. Safe Grinder ends Week 2 at `50` sanity instead of sliding further downward.
+- The core poverty-trap credit math remains unchanged despite that sanity swing: another `₡252` gross week still resolves to only `+₡172` net after burn, while hunger climbs from `20%` to `40%`.
+- The deterministic `Sanitation-T3` plus `Work Shift x3` baseline still holds through Week 2 without any food or hustle detour, so the first nontrivial event changed mood pressure but did not force a route deviation.
+
+## Blockers / Follow-Ups
